Cells were viewed with a 40× Fluor objective lens (Nikon), and a single cell (10–12 µm diameter) was fixed in a window positioned between the photomultiplier and the microscope. The changes in fluorescence ratios at 340 and 380 nm excitation wavelengths were measured using a CAM-200 spectrometer (Jasco, Japan). The absolute value of [Ca]in was calculated using the formulae as given by Grynkiewicz et al. [26]: \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
